        <div class="step reveal">
          <div class="step-num">01</div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <div class="step-name">Site Visit & Quote</div>
            <div class="step-desc">We visit, measure, assess the existing bathroom, discuss your brief, and provide a detailed fixed quote ‚Äî usually within 48 hours.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="step reveal">
          <div class="step-num">02</div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <div class="step-name">Demolition</div>
            <div class="step-desc">Full strip-out of existing floor, walls, ceiling, and fittings. All waste removed from site. Clean slate for new construction.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="step reveal">
          <div class="step-num">03</div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <div class="step-name">Mason Work</div>
            <div class="step-desc">Wall niches formed, floor concrete and screed laid, vanity top constructed, and wall plastering completed. No structural changes ‚Äî inspected before next stage.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="step reveal">
          <div class="step-num">04</div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <div class="step-name">Plumbing & Electrical Rough-in</div>
            <div class="step-desc">All supply, drain, and electrical rough-in completed and tested before walls are closed. No chasing walls open later.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="step reveal">
          <div class="step-num">05</div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <div class="step-name">Waterproofing</div>
            <div class="step-desc">Full membrane applied across all wet areas ‚Äî floor and walls. Allowed to fully cure before tiling begins. Critical step, never skipped.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="step reveal">
          <div class="step-num">06</div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <div class="step-name">Tiling</div>
            <div class="step-desc">Floor, walls, shower recess tiled with tile leveling system. Waterproof Swisstek grout applied throughout. Full clean-up.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="step reveal">
          <div class="step-num">07</div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <div class="step-name">Ceiling & Finishing</div>
            <div class="step-desc">Waterproof ceiling installed and finished. Electrical trims fitted. All surfaces inspected and any snags addressed.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="step reveal">
          <div class="step-num">08</div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <div class="step-name">Fixtures & Handover</div>
            <div class="step-desc">All client-supplied fittings installed and commissioned. Final walkthrough with you ‚Äî bathroom ready to use.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ -->
  <section class="faq-section">
    <div class="section-inner faq-inner">
      <div class="stag">Common Questions</div>
      <h2>Bathroom Renovation FAQ</h2>
      <div class="faqs">
        <div class="faq reveal">
          <div class="faq-q">How is the bathroom area measured for pricing?</div>
          <div class="faq-a">We measure the internal floor area of the bathroom in square feet. The Rs. 15,000/sq.ft rate is applied to this total floor area. Larger bathrooms naturally benefit from this rate as the fixed costs spread across more area ‚Äî contact us for any size queries.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq reveal">
          <div class="faq-q">Why is waterproofing so important?</div>
          <div class="faq-a">Waterproofing is the single most critical stage of any bathroom renovation in Sri Lanka's humid climate. A missed or inadequate membrane leads to water ingress into the structure within months. We never skip or skimp on this step ‚Äî full membrane application is standard on every project.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq reveal">
          <div class="faq-q">How long does a full bathroom renovation take?</div>
          <div class="faq-a">A standard bathroom (30‚Äì50 sq.ft) typically takes 10‚Äì15 working days depending on scope. We confirm the timeline during the site visit and keep you updated throughout.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq reveal">
          <div class="faq-q">Can you advise on tile selection?</div>
          <div class="faq-a">Yes ‚Äî we're happy to advise on tile sizes, formats, and finishes that suit your bathroom dimensions and your brief. We work alongside your tile supplier, or can recommend suppliers if needed.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq reveal">
          <div class="faq-q">Do you handle new bathroom builds as well as renovations?</div>
          <div class="faq-a">Yes ‚Äî our full scope covers both new bathroom construction (where no bathroom existed before) and complete renovations of existing bathrooms. The process and pricing approach is the same.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq reveal">
          <div class="faq-q">Is the price fixed once agreed?</div>
          <div class="faq-a">Yes ‚Äî once we've done the site visit and issued a quote, that price is fixed for the agreed scope. Any additions or changes to scope during the project are priced and agreed with you before work proceeds.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CTA />
  <Footer />
</Layout>

